** I am full of gratitude
------------------------------------------------------------
Good morning. I know three emails in three days is a lot, but before you frantically search for the "unsubscribe" button, this will be it from me for a while!

I woke up this morning full of gratitude. I may have cried a little, but in a good way. So many people supported yesterday's publication of Evil Roman Emperors; I just had to sneak in one more note to say thank you.

Here's what's next for me: keep trying to nudge the book up the sales ranks, and now - critically - asking friends to leave those precious five-star reviews (well, if they think the book so warrants it). Lots of work still to do, but my goodness, what a day yesterday. Have I said thank you? Thank you!!

If anyone is still looking for the book, you can find it, HERE (https://www.amazon.com/Evil-Roman-Emperors-Shocking-Caligula/dp/1633886905/ref=tmm_pap_swatch_0?_encoding=UTF8&qid=&sr=) .

Thank you all, and have a truly lovely day.

Phillip

(P.S. replies to these goofy emails make my day, so please reply and say hello. I just won't be sending any out for a while because you've all been very patient with me!)

